&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Consultant in Child and Adolescent Psychiatry Crisis Team&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Sowenna, Bodmin, Cornwall &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;10 Pas&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Permanent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Salary £82,096 - £110,683&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;National terms and conditions &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for the above post. This appointment forms part of a total of approx 40 consultants across the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cornwall Partnership NHS Foundation Trust is a forward looking and dynamic organisation, which is seeking to continuously improve its services – recently rated ‘Good’ by the CQC. Relationships between clinical staff and managers are underpinned by a determination to work together and with key external partners to ensure that we offer fair, personal, effective and safe services for service users, their carers and families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Treatment is co-ordinated by a case manager and can involve a wide range of psychological interventions as well as medical psychiatric treatment when appropriate. Treatment also often involves liaison with colleagues in other agencies to establish the best care package for the individual child or family.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full details of the Trust’s Children’s Services can be found in the job description.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Locum Consultant Psychiatrist is not expected to carry a care co-ordination caseload but will be available at short notice to provide consultation for the most complex and unstable cases and advice to other team members.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a well-qualified individual, with MRCPsych or equivalent, eligible for inclusion on the Specialist Register for Child and Adolescent Psychiatry and entitled to Section 12 / Responsible Clinician approval. You must be able to fulfil the travel requirements of the post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Appointment will be subject to the standard NHS employment checks including an enhanced Disclosure Barring Service (DBS) check.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;For the full job description click on the link to ‘Job Description’&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal enquiries to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Adrian Flynn Dr Tim Hawkins&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Medical Director Consultant Child and Adolescent Psychiatrist&lt;/p&gt;
